article.headline: Utah Valley St. 64, Grambling St. 34
article.story: OREM, Utah -- Isiah Williams and Alfonzo Hubbard scored 12 points each and Utah Valley breezed to a 64-34 win over Grambling State Wednesday night. The Wolverines (2-1) scored the last 18 points of the first half to lead 34-10 at intermission. Geddes Robinson, Keith Thompson and Ben Aird scored eight points apiece for Utah Valley. Utah Valley never trailed and held the Tigers (0-3) to 15 percent shooting (4 of 26) in the first half. Steven Danridge led Grambling State with 10 points. The Tigers had a better shooting second half, at 37 percent, but finished at 26 percent overall compared to the Wolverines' 48 percent from the field.
